 <!-- ============= Introduction ============================== -->
 <chapter id="introduction">
  <title>Introduction</title>
  <para>
  <application>Anjuta</application> is a versatile Integrated Development Environment 
  (IDE) for C and C++. It has been written for GTK/GNOME, and features 
  a number of advanced programming features. It is a graphical interface to the 
  collection of command line programming tools available for Linux and UNIX systems. 
  These are usually run via a text console, and can be unfriendly to use.
  </para>

  <para>
  <application>Anjuta</application> is an effort to marry the flexibility and power 
  of command line tools with the ease-of-use of the GNOME graphical user 
  interface. It has been made as user-friendly as possible.
  </para>

